def standardize(train, test):
    mu=sum(train)/len(train)
    var=sum((x-mu)**2 for x in train)/len(train)
    sd=var**0.5
    z=lambda v:[(x-mu)/sd for x in v]
    return z(train), z(test)
print(standardize([10,20,30,40], [25])[1])   # [-0.447...]
```

Without scaling, a feature measured in thousands dominates one measured in fractions — KNN/SVM distances and gradient-descent steps get skewed toward the large-magnitude feature. **Critical rule:** compute μ and σ on the **training set only**, then apply them to validation/test. Fitting the scaler on all data leaks test information into training and inflates your scores.

